catalog.title: Principles of Med Chem 2
catalog.description: MCH 502 is a continuation of MCH 501. Drug metabolism, prodrugs and drug delivery systems are discussed in detail. In addition, prototypes of selected drug classes are discussed with a focus on the molecular mechanisms of action of representative drugs. Drug-target interactions at the molecular level will be examined. In this course, the medicinal chemistry topics are integrated with relevant topics in biochemistry, pharmaceutics, and structural biology.
catalog.subject: Medicinal Chemistry

catalog.title: Protein & Peptide Chem
catalog.description: The class will discuss various topics on protein and peptide chemistry such as solid phase peptide synthesis, protein structure and design, peptide nucleic acids, peptoids, and betapeptides. Basic understanding of proteins will be provided as a foundation, followed by a discussion of recent papers focusing on the structure, function, and design aspects.
